First, to make different criteria have the same range of measurement, the costs and criterion values are normalized into the numbers from 0 to 1 respectively. Let O¯=(o¯1,o¯2,...,o¯m) be the vector of normalized costs, where o¯i is the normalized cost of response action Ai, i=1,2,…,m. Let d¯j=(d¯j1,d¯j2,…,d¯jq) be the vector of normalized criterion values, where d¯jk is the normalized criterion value concerning Dk with respect to scenario Sj, j=0,1,2,…,n, k=1,2,…,q. The calculation formulas of o¯i and d¯jk can be respectively expressed by(9)o¯i=omax−oiomax−omin,i=1,2,…,m
(10)d¯jk=dkmax−djkdkmax−dkmin,j=0,1,2,…,n,k=1,2,…,qwhere omax=max{o1,o2,…,om} and omin=min{o1,o2,…,om}; dkmax=max{
d0k,d1k,d2k,…,
dnk} and dkmin=min{
d0k,d1k,d2k,…,
dnk}. By Eqs. (9) and (10), the costs and criterion values are all unified into benefit type [30], [31], i.e., the greater o¯i is, the better action Ai will be; similarly, the greater d¯jk is, the better damage result concerning Dk with respect to scenario Sj will be.
